    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Float lamps used especially in churches or temples, having a cup or vase-shaped reservoir of colored glass or metal. By tradition and eccliastical dictate, it is mandatory for Jewish temples and many Chrisitan churches to have a constantly burning oil lamp in the sanctuary, in the vicinity of the tabernacle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
